%U A397666 21286277399918,140318635303468,925932197466898,6115834918940368,40430891024906563,267499767060144163
%N A397666 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} binomial(3*k-4,k).
%F A397666 G.f.: 1/(g^4 * (1-3*x*g^2) * (1-x)) where g = 1+x*g^3 is the g.f. of A001764.
%F A397666 G.f.: 1/((3-2*g) * (1-g+g^3)) where g = 1+x*g^3 is the g.f. of A001764.
%F A397666 Here and below, binomial(N,k) = 0 for k<0.
%F A397666 This is the special case l=0, m=3, c=0, r=1, s=0 of the following family. For integers l, m, c in Z, and for any constants r and s, define a_{l,m,c,r,s}(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} (r*binomial(l*n+m*k-m-1+c,k) - s*binomial(l*n+m*k-m-1+c,k-1)). A_{l,m,c,r,s}(x) = Sum_{n>=0} a_{l,m,c,r,s}(n)*x^n = t^c*(r+s-s*t)/((l+m-(l+m-1)*t)*(1-t+t^m)), where t = t(x) satisfies t = 1 + x*t^(l+m), equivalently y = x*(1+y)^(l+m) with y=t-1.
%F A397666 2*n*(2*n-5)*a(n) - (n-1)*(31*n-60)*a(n-1) + 3*(3*n-4)*(3*n-5)*a(n-2) = 0 for n > 2.
%o A397666 (PARI) a(n) = sum(k=0, n, binomial(3*k-4, k));
